data.title: EXCLUSIVE: Whoopi Goldberg wants to cast Jennifer Hudson for new Sister Act - and is keen to 'figure out money' and 'move fast' with production after SAG-AFTRA strikes are over: 'She is not going to l
data.meta_description: Speaking exclusively to DailyMail.com, a source claimed Whoopi believes casting Oscar-winner Jennifer is a 'no-brainer,' as acting veteran is keen to crack on with production.
data.text:
Whoopi Goldberg is determined to bring Sister Act 3 to screens, according to insiders, with the star especially keen on casting 'no-brainer' Jennifer Hudson.

The View co-host, 67, is set to reprise her role as the beloved Deloris Van Cartier - aka Sister Mary Clarence - for a third instalment, 30 years after the original blockbuster hit screens.

The long awaited project was greenlit in December 2020, and Whoopi is reportedly keen to 'figure out' the finances and 'move fast' with the production - which hit a 'stoplight' owing to the ongoing SAG-AFTRA strikes.

'One person that Whoopi would like to add to the film is Jennifer Hudson, especially after seeing what Jennifer did with the character when she did Sister Act for Halloween last year on her show,' a source told DailyMail.com exclusively.

'It would be a no-brainer to get Jennifer, Whoopi would really love for that to happen.'

Indeed, Jennifer dazzled The View cohost - and Sister Act fans - last year when she dressed up as Whoopi's famous character to deliver a breathtaking medley from the film franchise.

At the time, Whoopi had nothing but praise for the star's tribute and joked on The View that she might lose her role to the EGOT winner.

The insider continued: 'The new Sister Act is going to happen. They have the idea, they have Whoopi. Once the strikes are done, they are ready to make the film for the fans and a new generation.

'They aren't at a dead end; they are more at a stoplight. They have to figure out money, and who to cast but Whoopi is very anxious to get the ball rolling and she feels once Hollywood gets back to work, Sister Act will then move fast.'

They claimed the recent 'success and fanfare' of Hocus Pocus 2 has spurred bosses on to get the film out to the fans.

'It will happen. Whoopi is not going to let this die. Everything comes back - Coming to America came back!'

The insider also claimed the film will be a 'celebration' with an 'endless number of cameos.'

'Fun times are coming,' they said. 'Whoopi is ready and already has a handful of nun puns for the tagline and what they want to name the film.'

The actress has previously been vocal about her desire to see Dame Maggie Smith reprise her role as the Mother Superior for one last hurrah.

Speaking to UK panel show Loose Women in January, the Ghost star explained: 'You know, one of the things that I want to make sure I do while I'm here is.

'I want to let Maggie Smith know that I'm holding the part of Mother Superior for you. Because I just can't do it with anybody but you.'

She then added: 'So if you need me to come over here [to England] and shoot and do whatever we have to do, we will do whatever you want us to do, but we don't want to do it without you.'

Whoopi continued: 'I'm liking the script, you know we're all going to do whatever we have to do. I'm trying to secure a director!'

It's not the first time Whoopi, real moniker Caryn Elaine Johnson, has reached out to her former co-star, having also made a plea during an appearance on the BBC's The One Show last year.

Elsewhere, actress and singer Keke Palmer expressed her desire to star in the film after she shared a fan-made poster, which claimed she had been cast alongside Whoopi and Bette Midler.

'God bless y'all for this manifestation over my life. @WaltDisneyCo, this is what they asked for I'm just here to relay,' she wrote on Twitter.

Whoopi shared the same fake poster as she warned fans that it was false casting - but confirmed that the film was still very much in production.

Last month, Whoopi hinted that the Vatican City could be the location of the upcoming film, during a visit to see the Pope.

She asked her 1.3 million followers to 'picture Sister Act and all the nuns standing here and waiting for the Pope to come out' as she stood in front of St. Peter's Square.

She continued: 'Maybe that's going to happen in the movie - you never know. But we are in Rome and we are in Vatican City.'

Disney officially announced in 2020 that a follow up to 1992's Sister Act and 1993's Sister Act 2: Back in the Habit was in the works.

Billionaire producer Tyler Perry has also signed on for the project and previously stated: 'We've got a good script....

'We're just trying to get everybody moving in the right direction to get it going.'

Jimmy Fallon threw himself into the ring for a cameo appearance while Whoopi's The View cohosts Joy Behar, Sara Haines, Sunny Hostin and Alyssa Farrah Griffin joked that they 'could be nuns also.'
